Notebook[{
Cell["Metric Algebra", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"f6920709-e3ac-44e2-869d-057b92cf9d9b"],

Cell["\<\
The metric-algebra layer is the quantitative substrate that sits under the \
synthetic Euclidean and Tarski layers. It exposes the master interval \
function I(u, v), the geodesic-multiplicity matrix, a tropical-idempotence \
test for distance matrices, and the metric median -- the algebraic objects \
that the higher layers query through one-equation conditions on the distance \
matrix D and the cost-adjacency matrix A. The min-plus arithmetic that this \
layer rests on (TropicalPlus, TropicalTimes, TropicalDot, TropicalMatrixPower) \
is documented separately in TropicalOperationsGuide.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"511ec069-7054-4a51-a234-ed3688b91802"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3e9642e0-d8bf-4ff6-9e61-31cc3c53fcb4"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"103ee817-305e-4d1e-b4dc-132f6bfc2df9"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"e55b82d4-3890-4617-8104-1e011cc820e1"],

Cell["Master operation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3ed568c5-38d6-4a9e-9889-a54b2c1bcb02"],

Cell["\<\
MetricInterval -- the geodesic interval I(u, v) = { w : d(u, w) + d(w, v) = \
d(u, v) }, i.e. the union of all geodesics from u to v. Every other primitive \
in this layer (and the Tarski betweenness predicate) reduces to it.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3dcc6d27-f53a-48ff-a914-ce0893cf3282"],

Cell["Geodesic counts and multiplicities", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0e0ddedb-e24c-4f59-8cd9-06202492d60f"],

Cell["\<\
GeodesicCount -- the number of geodesics between u and v, computed in \
polynomial time as (A^d)[u, v] where d = d(u, v). Walks of length d(u, v) \
from u to v are automatically simple geodesics.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3b31b454-6223-420c-91b0-b064c923a862"],

Cell["\<\
DistanceMultiplicityMatrix -- the pair (D, M): D is the graph distance \
matrix, M[i, j] = (A^{D[i,j]})[i, j] counts geodesics. The multiplicity \
counterpart of the metric.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"538e0b12-7632-46f2-9e3e-a32ca5abe2ec"],

Cell["Distance-matrix axiomatics", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"185ac01d-0d1a-4924-916a-c1eb6aae7b7b"],

Cell["\<\
DistanceMatrixQ -- tests whether a square non-negative symmetric \
zero-diagonal matrix M is the distance matrix of some graph, via the \
tropical-idempotence form of the triangle inequality M (x)_min M = M.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e6845863-1621-4b19-8783-634cf4553fa5"],

Cell["Metric centroids", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6e424bf5-4749-4e70-ac3d-7f4efa421a06"],

Cell["\<\
MedianVertices -- the metric medians of a vertex set vs: argmin over w of the \
total distance Sum d(w, x) for x in vs. A graph is a median graph iff every \
triple has a unique median.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"01c84094-55fb-4163-a581-14c07758fd03"],

Cell["Examples", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"eedf5c43-0661-4236-b6c3-462422b75040"],

Cell["\<\
The geodesic interval between opposite corners of a 3 x 3 grid.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"95fe2156-f150-4a21-b8ab-ed559b975147"],

Cell["MetricInterval[GridGraph[{3, 3}], 1, 9]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a7ec321f-96d0-49db-934e-f4cfb6b20ec9"],

Cell["\<\
Number of geodesics between two corners of a 4 x 4 grid -- the central \
binomial coefficient C(6, 3) = 20.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"71a300bc-f289-434c-8031-e0403e44e016"],

Cell["GeodesicCount[GridGraph[{4, 4}], 1, 16]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"c71aa631-6d25-477b-af5c-fb5db062db33"],

Cell["Distance and multiplicity matrices of the cycle C_5.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"c332649e-3c45-453e-bd2c-73e58c4213b3"],

Cell["DistanceMultiplicityMatrix[CycleGraph[5]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a7355167-303b-49ec-a1f3-db328fa1181a"],

Cell["Tropical idempotence test on the distance matrix of a path.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"6d46bf2d-097c-4055-8c72-7d88835eb7e6"],

Cell["DistanceMatrixQ[GraphDistanceMatrix[PathGraph[Range[5]]]]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"c98ec112-f3a8-4757-8eed-3a933bf8958d"],

Cell["Median vertices of a triple in a tree.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"0f9fc627-29fe-4321-bf1e-afc59388ff77"],

Cell["MedianVertices[CompleteGraph[{2, 3}], {1, 2, 3}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"405684e3-7119-45e0-8db5-1af5068a38ae"],

Cell["Synthetic-to-analytic-to-algebraic", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b78996a3-30d7-4cc0-9de4-289a7d5683a4"],

Cell["\<\
The progression: synthetic graph G is encoded as the cost-adjacency matrix A \
(zero on the diagonal, one on edges, Infinity off-edge). Tropical \
exponentiation TropicalMatrixPower[A, k] stabilises at k = diam(G) to the \
graph distance matrix D = GraphDistanceMatrix[G], and TropicalDot[D, D] === \
D is the matrix form of the triangle inequality (DistanceMatrixQ uses \
exactly this check). The pair (A, D) under the ordinary and tropical \
semirings carries walk counts and walk distances respectively, and every \
metric primitive in the higher layers reduces to a one-line query on (A, D).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"549f1efa-7241-4f91-a8f6-eb1582418f4e"],

